peer_feedback_assignment_2:
  issue_number: 29
  issue_owner: jackeee101
  issue_ok: yes
  issue_status: OK
  overall_comments:
    positive: The Op-Ed section is a strong highlight, as it clearly interprets the
      data and connects it to a real-world policy discussion in a meaningful way.
    negative: The code could be made more efficient and readable by consolidating
      repeated transformations and improving organization.
    advice: Combine repeated mutate() statements into a single step, and enhance table
      formatting with clearer labels and summaries to improve readability.
  scores:
    Written Communication:
      score: 7.0
      comment: The writing is clear and easy to follow, and the Op-Ed does a good
        job connecting the analysis to the SFFA decision. However, some sections are
        a bit repetitive and could benefit from more concise explanations and stronger
        transitions between ideas.
    Project Skeleton:
      score: 7.0
      comment: The project follows the expected structure and completes all required
        tasks. One improvement would be reducing repeated mutate() steps by combining
        them into a single transformation to make the code more efficient and readable.
    Tables & Document Presentation:
      score: 7.0
      comment: The tables are functional and display the required results clearly.
        To improve presentation, adding clearer titles, captions, or formatting enhancements
        would make them more polished.
    Data Visualization:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Exploratory Data Analysis:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Code Quality:
      score: 7.0
      comment: The code is generally correct and uses appropriate dplyr pipelines.
        However, there is some redundancy (multiple sequential mutate() calls) that
        could be streamlined for better efficiency and clarity.
    Data Preparation:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Analysis and Findings:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The analysis answers the required questions and includes thoughtful
        interpretation in the Op-Ed. It could be strengthened by more explicitly linking
        the findings back to the SFFA decision and discussing potential limitations
        of the analysis.
    Extra Credit:
      score: 0.0
      comment: no extra credit was done
  mp_number: 1
peer_feedback_assignment_3:
  issue_number: 42
  issue_owner: er0driguez
  issue_ok: yes
  issue_status: OK
  overall_comments:
    positive: The Op-Ed is a standout feature, combining strong narrative writing
      with data-driven insights and effective use of inline values.
    negative: Some parts of the code and analysis are slightly repetitive, and could
      be streamlined for better efficiency and clarity.
    advice: Refactor repeated calculations into reusable transformations and consider
      adding brief summaries after key outputs to guide the reader.
  scores:
    Written Communication:
      score: 9.0
      comment: The writing is clear, engaging, and well-structured, especially in
        the Op-Ed section which connects the analysis to real-world implications effectively.
        The narrative flows well, though a few sections could be slightly more concise
        to improve readability.
    Project Skeleton:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The project is very well organized and follows a clear structure from
        data acquisition through analysis and interpretation. The use of modular code
        and consistent pipelines makes the workflow easy to follow.
    Tables & Document Presentation:
      score: 9.0
      comment: The tables are well-formatted and visually polished, with clear labels
        and thoughtful use of formatting. The addition of styling and summaries improves
        readability and gives the document a professional look.
    Data Visualization:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Exploratory Data Analysis:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Code Quality:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The code is clean, well-structured, and uses tidyverse functions effectively.
        There is good use of across() and pipelines, though some repeated calculations
        could be abstracted into reusable steps for efficiency.
    Data Preparation:
      score: 10.0
      comment: DEFAULT SCORE
    Analysis and Findings:
      score: 8.0
      comment: The analysis is thoughtful and goes beyond basic requirements by connecting
        trends to both SFFA and comparisons with other institutions. The interpretation
        is strong, though briefly discussing limitations or assumptions would strengthen
        the conclusions.
    Extra Credit:
      score: 1.0
      comment: This submission includes a well-formatted visualization that supports
        the Op-Ed analysis, so 1 point of extra credit is awarded.
  mp_number: 1
